    <h2>Why should I buy/build a 3D printed violin instead?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>It's sturdier than standard violins and individual pieces can be easily replaced if broken.</li>
      <li>You can customize the violin's shape and color.</li>
      <li>3D printing is sooo cool.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Do you have a place where you archive your designs and keep track of future enhancements? Can I make a feature request?</h2>
    <p>The violin's 3D model files are available via github. Please post any feature requests or issues <a href="https://github.com/matthova/hovalin-files/issues">here.</a></p>

    <h2>Where's the chinrest?</h2>
    <p>That's a great example of a feature request. Check out the progress <a href="https://github.com/matthova/hovalin-files/issues">here.</a></p>


    <h2>Do I need to re-orient the model to make it fit? Does the Hovalin fit on my printer?</h2>
    <p>Each .stl is oriented to be flush with the print bed. If it doesn't fit, it may need to be rotated slightly. Depending on the printer, the part may be too big for your printer.</p>


    <h2>We're having a hard time getting the strings to stay in their grooves</h2>
    <p>This is tricky. <a href="/make/#install-strings">Per the instructions</a>, make sure that the string winds down to the bottom of the tuning peg. It will take some guesswork, and it may take multiple tries, but it should work. Let us know if you run into any unsolvable issue or if you come up with any cool techniques for solving this obstacle.</p>


    <h2>Do I need to generate support to print the violin?</h2>
    <p>No support is necessary to print the violin.</p>


    <h2>Have you tried printing the violin with "________ Material"?</h2>
    <p>Thus far, we've only printed the violin in PLA. If you print the violin in any other material, share the photos/videos! We'd love to hear about your experiences.</p>


    <h2>Does altering the infill or print settings change the sound quality?</h2>
